    { name: 'Nifedipine', purpose: 'Emergency treatment for High-Altitude Pulmonary Edema (HAPE). Calcium channel blocker that reduces pulmonary artery pressure.', dosage: '20mg slow-release, then 20mg every 6 hours. For emergency use only.', notes: 'Prescription only. Can cause sudden blood pressure drop. Do not use with altitude sickness unless HAPE is specifically diagnosed. Does not replace descent.' },
